olive oil
2 potato
½ lemon
2 clove garlic
25 g butter
1 tomato
1 white turnip
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet roasted almonds
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet garlic aioli

• Bring a medium saucepan of lightly salted water to the boil. Cut potato into
large chunks. Slice lemon into wedges. Finely chop garlic.
• Cook potato in boiling water until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
• Return saucepan to medium-high heat, then add the butter and garlic and
cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute. Add a generous squeeze of lemon
juice and a pinch of salt, then bring to boil. Remove from heat, then return
potato to the pan and toss to coat. Lightly crush potato with a potato
masher or fork. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato. Thinly slice turnip. Place your hand flat
on top of each chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two
thin steaks. Crush roasted almonds in a mortar and pestle, or in their sachet
using a rolling pin until resembling fine crumbs.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken steaks, crushed almonds, garlic &
herb seasoning, a good drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of pepper. Turn and
press chicken to coat in almond crumb.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if
your pan is getting crowded).

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

TIP: Don't worry if some of the crumbs fall off, sprinkle them back on chicken
when serving!

• While the chicken is cooking, combine tomato, turnip, mixed leaves and a
drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.
• Divide almond and garlic-crusted chicken, lemon crushed potatoes and
turnip salad between plates.
• Serve with garlic aioli and any remaining lemon wedges.